   <xs:complexType name="extract">
      <xs:annotation>
         <xs:documentation>
            <xd:section xmlns:xd="http://www.oecd.org/ns/schema/xdocs">
               <xd:title>Categories</xd:title>
               <xd:p>structural, block</xd:p>
            </xd:section> Extract structural block <xd:section xmlns:xd="http://www.oecd.org/ns/schema/xdocs">
               <xd:title>Definition</xd:title>
               <xd:p>Extracts represent one of two related inter document relationships. The first of these is
                  embedding all or part of a document into the current document. This can range from a block
                  quote (one or more paragraphs of text from an externalsource) from legislation in an
                  official document to the inclusion of an entire official document as part of another
                  official document. The second is linking where the content is not included into the
                  reference document until the time at which it is rendered.</xd:p>
            </xd:section>
         </xs:documentation>
      </xs:annotation>
