         <xs:documentation>
            <xd:section xmlns:xd="http://www.oecd.org/ns/schema/xdocs">
               <xd:title>Categories</xd:title>
               <xd:p>semantic, structural</xd:p>
            </xd:section> Glossary semantic structural Notes Glossaries are term/definition lists. Governance
            or resource question: what glossaries can be made available to authors and what tuning/granularity
            is needed to make the use of them efficiently within a given subject area or directorate? Product
            question: is it possible to have business rules automatically applied for glossary candidates or
            acronym mistakes, etc.? </xs:documentation>
      </xs:annotation>
      <xs:sequence>
         <xs:choice maxOccurs="unbounded">
            <xs:element name="section" type="section"/>
         </xs:choice>
      </xs:sequence>
   </xs:complexType>
   <xs:complexType name="abbreviation-list">
      <xs:annotation>
         <xs:documentation>
