   <xs:complexType name="formatting-tag">
      <xs:annotation>
         <xs:documentation>
            <xd:section xmlns:xd="http://www.oecd.org/ns/schema/xdocs">
               <xd:title>Categories</xd:title>
               <xd:p>inline</xd:p>
            </xd:section> Formatting Tag inline <xd:section xmlns:xd="http://www.oecd.org/ns/schema/xdocs">
               <xd:title>Notes</xd:title>
               <xd:p>Any simple formatting (italicisation without any particular semantic load for
                  example).</xd:p>
            </xd:section>
            <xd:section xmlns:xd="http://www.oecd.org/ns/schema/xdocs">
               <xd:title>Definition</xd:title>
               <xd:p>Semantic models of text normally do not provide any way of indicating formatting. The new
                  OECD.Author model must provide some way to indicate simple inline formatting requirements
                  because the current AE2007 environment allows it. Therefore, the modelling workshop agreed
                  that some sort of simple formatting must be allowed.</xd:p>
               <xd:p>No decision on the implementation of this component has been decided. As formatting
                  options are in many ways open ended, we suggest that a single formatting element would be
                  advisable with the precise requested rendering indicated via properties (defined by a set of
                  values taken from an enumerated list)</xd:p>
            </xd:section>
         </xs:documentation>
